The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Punters Corner - RCTC CEO resigns
                                                                                                               RCTC CEO resigns 
            STAR RACER                        
	Calcutta: Lieutenant Gen (retd) J. R. Mukherjee, CEO RCTC, is learnt to have put in his papers on Sunday. His resignation followed an insulting remark made by a club member who insisted on using his celphone at the RCTC ground, without paying the required fees. The use of celphones at the racecourse is permitted only after a daily payment of Rs 1,500.           
	Gen. Mukherjees contributions towards the upliftment of the club from the dumps is well ackowledged in the RCTC circles. Asked to comment on the issue, Cyrus Madan, chairman RCTC said. Its a very unfortunate incident. Im upset, angry and cheesed off. Another senior member, who did not wish to be identified, added: Had such an incident happened in any other club, a serious disciplinary action would have been taken against the guilty member. He may have even been shown the door.                                                                                                                                                                         
